Google is set to unveil the Pixel 3 smartphone on 9 October 2018, according to reports. There have been several leaks detailing information about the Pixel 3 of late, with industry sources claiming the smartphone will run Android 9.0 out of the box. Google is also set to unveil a new display design which features a notch – an element popularised by Apple with its iPhone X. The company is expected to maintain its two-device launch format, with a Pixel 3 and Pixel 3 XL coming. Snapdragon 845 chips and 6GB of RAM are reported to power the devices.